name: 朱利尔斯·周

last_movies.title: 汪汪队立大功之勇敢大营救

introduction: Julius Cho is a CSA-nominated Canadian actor, voice artist, and performer, renowned for his versatile roles in both live-action and animated projects. He is best known for portraying Jean Luc on CTV's Children Ruin Everything, as well as Yoshi in Netflix's Wedding Season. Julius made his SXSW debut with the acclaimed film Sweetness, showcasing his range in both dramatic and comedic roles. In addition to his on-screen success, he has lent his voice to popular animated series such as Paw Patrol, Total Drama Island, My Little Pony, and Bakugan. With a career that spans television, film, and voice work, Julius continues to captivate audiences with his dynamic performances and is quickly becoming one of Canada's most exciting talents.
